The paper focuses on distributed coordination control of multi-agent systems, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. The most relevant sub-category is likely cs.SY (Systems and Control), which deals with the analysis and design of complex systems, including multi-agent systems. The paper also heavily relies on graph theory, which is a fundamental tool in many areas of computer science, including cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) and cs.RO (Robotics). Additionally, the paper discusses topics such as consensus, formation control, and swarming/flocking, which are related to networked systems and algorithms, and could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.DS (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
